Package: HydroMetDB
Title: Hydrological database creation and maintenance
Version: 1.8.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ghislain", "de Laplante", , "ghislain.delaplante@yukon.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5093-9185")),
    person("Emilie", "Stewart-Jones", , "emilie.stewart-jones@yukon.ca", role = "aut",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0013-8953"))
  )
Description: Set of functions for the creation and ongoing maintenance of
    the Yukon Government's hydrometeorological database in postgreSQL
    format. This database is a combination of the Water Survey of Canada
    real-time and historical data, YG data held in Aquarius and in the
    RWIS database, USGS data, discrete snow survey data, and water quality data. Supports any
    number of timeseries unique by their location, parameter, data type,
    and period (for sum, mean, etc measurements). Disparate data sources
    are handled via scripts specified for each timeseries, allowing for
    expansion of data sources.
